<p><strong>ITEM #:</strong> SCP-<span class="numba1">5</span><span class="numba2">6</span><span class="numba3">4</span><span class="numba4">6</span></p>
<p><strong>OBJECT CLASS: </strong><span id="truth">Fluxus</span></p>
<p><strong>SPECIAL CONTAINMENT PROCEDURES:</strong> SCP-<span class="numba1">5</span><span class="numba2">6</span><span class="numba3">4</span><span class="numba4">6</span><span ID="contain"> is not to remain open for passage, nor should it be closed or obstructed in a way that would prevent passage into the anomaly.</span></p>
<p>Personnel are heavily discouraged from traversing SCP-<span class="numba1">5</span><span class="numba2">6</span><span class="numba3">4</span><span class="numba4">6</span>, regardless of how passable it appears. SCP-<span class="numba1">5</span><span class="numba2">6</span><span class="numba3">4</span><span class="numba4">6</span> should be monitored via CCTV by the Site-<span ID="site">64</span> Security Division with equal scrutiny they would for any other part of the facility, and should report any personnel that enters SCP-<span class="numba1">5</span><span class="numba2">6</span><span class="numba3">4</span><span class="numba4">6</span> as lost.</p>
<p><strong>DESCRIPTION:</strong> SCP-<span class="numba1">5</span><span class="numba2">6</span><span class="numba3">4</span><span class="numba4">6</span> is a hallway in Site-<span ID="site2">64</span>, sublevel <span ID="level">27</span>. The anomaly has no doors or shutters, nor does the path linearly connect to any other part of the facility. The words &quot;DO NOT OBSTRUCT&quot; and &quot;DO NOT KEEP OPEN&quot; were found on the wall next to SCP-<span class="numba1">5</span><span class="numba2">6</span><span class="numba3">4</span><span class="numba4">6</span>'s entrance in non-anomalous acrylic gold lettering. No records of SCP-<span class="numba1">5</span><span class="numba2">6</span><span class="numba3">4</span><span class="numba4">6</span>'s construction have been found, nor does the hallway appear on any blueprints, inspection dossiers or personnel accounts prior to 1943. SCP-<span class="numba1">5</span><span class="numba2">6</span><span class="numba3">4</span><span class="numba4">6</span>'s destination is unknown, but as of the events of Incident <span class="numba1">5</span><span class="numba2">6</span><span class="numba3">4</span><span class="numba4">6</span>-A, documentation regarding the anomaly is subject to extreme narrativistic decoherence, suggesting <a href="https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/sandrewswann-s-proposal">[DATA EXPUNGED]</a>.</p>
<p><strong>INCIDENT LOG <span class="numba1">5</span><span class="numba2">6</span><span class="numba3">4</span><span class="numba4">6</span>-A:</strong> At approximately 09:45 on 10/28/1986, an individual identified as Level <span ID="clearance">3</span><span class="titled"> Foundation Researcher</span> Gene Halliburton was observed exiting from SCP-<span class="numba1">5</span><span class="numba2">6</span><span class="numba3">4</span><span class="numba4">6</span>. <span class="titled">Researcher</span> Halliburton was reported missing twelve days prior by an acquaintance while hiking near Boynton Canyon, AZ. According to eyewitness testimony, a flash flood had swept through their campsite and separated Halliburton from the rest of the group he was traveling with. He was presumed dead up until this point.</p>
<p><span class="titled">Researcher</span> Halliburton was swiftly detained and interrogated. An audio transcript of his testimony can be found below.</p>
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Interview <span class="numba1">5</span><span class="numba2">6</span><span class="numba3">4</span><span class="numba4">6</span>-A</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Interviewer:</strong> Hane Dougherty, Head of Logistics and Foundation Asset Management for Site-<span ID="site3">64</span></p>
<p><strong>Interviewee:</strong> Level <span ID="clearance2">3</span><span class="titled"> Researcher</span> Gene Halliburton</p>
<hr />
<p style="text-align:center;">&lt;BEGIN LOG&gt;</p>
<p><strong>Dougherty:</strong> Well, Gene—Let me first say that I'm happy to see you are alive and seemingly healthy.</p>
<p><strong>Halliburton:</strong> I feel fine—just don't see what all the fuss is about. You didn't need to bring out the whole cavalcade just for me.</p>
<p><strong>Dougherty:</strong> It's just standard procedure, nothing personal. Surely you must understand the... <em>gravitas</em> of you showing up like this?</p>
<p><strong>Halliburton:</strong> Is this because of the sign? Look, I didn't realize it was a big issue, the phrasing is kind of confusing. I thought it led to the commissary—at least, it is the right direction. I would know; I've had to carry a compass just to get around here without being late to everything.</p>
<p><strong>Dougherty:</strong> [pause] Gene, are you aware of the events of the last few weeks? Specifically, what happened when you were on PTO?</p>
<p><strong>Halliburton:</strong> Wha—of course I am. Is this a comment about my mental acuity? I'd remind you that jokes aren't jokes if they hurt feelings and we are in a harassment-free workplace. [pause] It was my daughter's birthday, Hane, I wouldnt forget that. We went to the beach. I took the next few days off and went to Vegas with the guys. Lost a couple hundred at the casino since I left my wallet next to the vending machines. Most expensive bag of Combos I've ever had.</p>
<p><strong>Dougherty:</strong> And what about Arizona? You must remember that.</p>
<p><strong>Halliburton:</strong> Yeah? What about it? It was a nice way to round off the trip. Weather was lovely. Got to see the vortex, which was almost certainly anomalous, by the way. We should probably look into that.</p>
<p><strong>Dougherty:</strong> I guess so. Well, while you were gone, Logistics updated the keycard readers and issued new codes. The old ones stop working throughout the day, so I'll need to update yours immediately if you don't want to get flagged every time you do so much as wash your hands.</p>
<p><strong>Halliburton:</strong> Ah, I guess that explains things.</p>
<p><em>Some rustling is heard.</em></p>
<p><strong>Halliburton:</strong> Here you go.</p>
<p><strong>Dougherty:</strong> Perfect, thank you. Just be a sec.</p>
<p><em>A few seconds of silence, followed by the sound of sliding plastic, ending on a series of out-of-key beeps.</em></p>
<p><strong>Dougherty:</strong> Hmmm.</p>
<p><em>Another plastic noise, followed by more flat tones.</em></p>
<p><strong>Halliburton:</strong> Is there a problem?</p>
<p><strong>Dougherty:</strong> It's probably this shoddy clearance handheld, they have spotty connections down here, I apologize. I'll get it done in a snap, hold tight.</p>
<p><em>Scraping and creaking as a chair is pushed back. Dougherty is heard getting up and leaving the room.</em></p>
<p><strong>Halliburton:</strong> [sighs]</p>
<p><em>Roughly two minutes of silence pass.</em></p>
<p><em>The door is heard opening, followed by a several pairs of footsteps.</em></p>
<p><strong>Security Personnel:</strong> Alright, let's go! Up! Now!</p>
<p><strong>Halliburton:</strong> What—?</p>
<p><em>Sounds of commotion, struggling.</em></p>
<p><strong>Halliburton:</strong> No, look at my badge, I—I'm a level <span ID="clearancespell">three</span>—[grunt]—fuck—LEVEL <span ID="clearancespellcap">THREE</span>! R&amp;D!—[groan]—</p>
<p><strong>Security Personnel:</strong> UP! When I say <em>let's go</em>, you <em>go</em>!</p>
<p><strong>Halliburton:</strong>—But—agh—I-I didn't do anything! [yelps]—I <em>didn't</em>—<em>do anything</em>!</p>
<p><em>Thirty seconds of struggle, accompanied by a dragging sound.</em></p>
<p><strong>Halliburton:</strong> H-HELP! Somebody help!—Please!—What are you going to do to me?—[sobs]—Let me go! Please, I want to see my family! M-MAGGIE!—[sobs]</p>
<p><em>Microphone records similar for the next few minutes. The commotion steadily grows quiet, and someone still in the room shuts off tape shortly thereafter.</em></p>
<p style="text-align:center;">&lt;END LOG&gt;</p>
<hr />
<p><em>Note: Subject continued to make frequent pleas to see his family until appropriate action was taken. Personnel dossier reveals no family by the names claimed by subject. Notably, the late researcher had no children. The appearance of a <span class="titled"> Researcher</span> Halliburton was determined to be unrelated to his disappearance; Halliburton has crossovered.</em></p>
</blockquote>
